{"title":"Avoiding pollution: 'healthy river code' scheme","public_updated_at":"2014-04-23T14:03:44Z","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The ‘healthy river code’ is an Environment Agency project (in England) that builds on an international approach to protecting the environment. The healthy river code uses a series of simple icons to demonstrate how to protect and preserve local rivers.</p>\n\n<p>The healthy river code is a set of communication tools that can be used to educate the public about their rivers, the impact of urban diffuse pollution and action they can take to avoid contributing to the problem. It is a standard set of graphics that explain to the public how to avoid polluting urban watercourses.</p>\n\n<p>Every single one of us can help look after the rivers and streams we all love by following the healthy river code.</p>\n\n<p>Healthy river code icons and visuals available for partners to download here:</p>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.theartdepartment.co.uk/love_your_river/\">Healthy river code campaign materials</a></p>\n\n</div>","change_history":[],"documents":["<section class=\"attachment embedded\" id=\"attachment_550170\">\n  <div class=\"attachment-thumb\">\n      <a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"thumbnail\" href=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/303779/HRC.pdf\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/303779/thumbnail_HRC.pdf.png\" /></a>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"attachment-details\">\n    <h2 class=\"title\"><a href=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/303779/HRC.pdf\">Healthy River Code</a></h2>\n    <p class=\"metadata\">\n        <span class=\"type\"><abbr title=\"Portable Document Format\">PDF</abbr></span>, <span class=\"file-size\">372KB</span>, <span class=\"page-length\">2 pages</span>\n    </p>\n\n\n  </div>\n</section>"],"emphasised_organisations":["16628142-57b2-4611-bc03-5912785acee3"],"political":false,"government":{"title":